$ libc: signal handling

{ Checking if ctrl-c was pressed. #libc-signal-sigint

  The → Linux/kernel/process/signal[signal] handler that is associated with
      → Linux/kernel/process/signal#sigint[`SIGINT`] is called when the user presses `ctrl-c`.

  The following code snipplet establishes a signal handler that traps the pressing of `ctrl-c` and writes a
  corresponding message to → development/stdin-stdout-stderr[stdout].

  gh|about-libc|/signal/SIGINT.c||

}
